      "date": "2013-11-07 22:08:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 10: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI ran this code on an OpenSFS node with the -a option. I was watching memory usage with /proc/meminfo and the memory dropped from 19698572 kB to 215280 kB adn then it just bounced between 200000 kB to 210000 kB, but wouldn't drop down to the advertised 100 kB. \n\nThen the code seg faulted.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
