          "date": "2013-07-12 05:40:07.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-2264 test: Create memory load for testing",
        "message": "LU-2264 test: Create memory load for testing\n\nIt can be useful to add extra memory pressure for testing.\nClient nodes are likely to use extra resources.\n\nrewrite memhog.c to include an automatic mode. ./memhog -a will\nconsume all but 160-128mb of Ram and Swap. The mode consumes\nthen exits at this time. Original behavior is maintained with\nthe exception of moving the chunk size to 32mb (down from 128m)\n\nSigned-off-by: Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I590b08479c559a846fee166d2c8ea28cbe6a89e4\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
